# The open-core @infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-* packages are published to GitHub
# Packages. They are PUBLIC, but GitHub's npm registry requires a token to
# install even public packages — so set GITHUB_TOKEN to a Personal Access Token
# with the `read:packages` scope. Any GitHub account can mint one; this is NOT
# gated on Infoblox org membership. Everything else installs anonymously from
# npmjs. (To iterate on the SDK itself instead, use the local `link:` fallback
# in the README.)
@infobloxopen:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
